post_text:
Dear CPS Community,

This morning, Governor Lamont, made an executive decision to close school for the remainder of the school year. CPS students will continue to participate in the Phase 3 Virtual Learning Plan for the remainder of the school year. The last day of Virtual Learning will be on June 15, 2020.

More information regarding graduation and promotion ceremonies along with other end of year activities will be forthcoming from school principals.

Thank you for all of your support during this very challenging time. We miss our students very much but understand that the governor’s decision to close school the remainder of the year was based on the safety of our students and staff.

It is my sincere hope that your families are healthy and safe.

Dr. Enza Macri
Superintendent
Cromwell Public Schools
text:
Dear CPS Community,

More information regarding graduation and promotion ceremonies along with other end of year activities will be forthcoming from school principals.

Thank you for all of your support during this very challenging time. We miss our students very much but understand that the governor’s decision to close school the remainder of the year was based on the safety of our students and staff.

It is my sincere hope that your families are healthy and safe.

Dr. Enza Macri
Superintendent
Cromwell Public Schools

post_text:
Happy School Lunch Hero Day to our Cromwell Public Schools front line HEROES – our dedicated Café Staff! Thank you so much for taking good care of our students and families! You do not only provide students with their basic needs of a healthy breakfast and lunch - you have also given our children the connection to our schools during this challenging time that they so greatly need. They look forward to seeing YOU!

My sincere gratitude,

Enza

Please enjoy this well-deserved article about our CPS School Lunch Heroes featured in Cromwell Life today. See link below.

https://view.publitas.com/p222-6222/cwl_200501_a/page/1
